AMD announced at Computex 2019 that it will launch its third-generation Ryzen processors on 7 July 2019. The chipmaker unveiled five new processors at the event, including its flagship Ryzen 9 3900X which boasts 12 cores and 24 threads. AMD compared the 3900X to the Intel i9-9920X, and claimed that the 3900X offers 16% more performance than the competing product. Two Ryzen 7 processors were also launched – the 3700X and 3800X. AMD said that the Ryzen 7 3700X is comparable to the i7-9700K, while the 3800X is comparable to the i7-9900K. Two more affordable third-generation Ryzen 5 processors were also launched. Below are the specifications of AMD’s new 3rd-generation Ryzen processors.